Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Vice President's Residence in Washington, D.C. during the National Governors Association (NGA) weekend. He expressed gratitude to the governors for their leadership and highlighted the importance of collaboration and cooperation between the federal government and state governments. Pence also discussed the administration's efforts to promote state-based flexibility, innovation, and reform, including in healthcare, land management, and combating opioid abuse. He emphasized the administration's commitment to working with governors on infrastructure legislation and cutting red tape. Pence praised the governors for their leadership during times of natural disasters and pledged continued partnership and support from the federal government. Pence concluded by thanking the governors for their service and expressing his respect and gratitude for the job they do.